http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Mon 11 Jun 2018
Source: OIE, WAHID (World Animal Health Information Database), weekly disease information 2018; 31(24) [edited]
http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review?page_refer=MapFullEventReport&reportid=26871


Equine influenza, Uruguay
-------------------------
Information received on [and dated] 11 Jun 2018 from Dr Eduardo Barre Albera, Director General, [Livestock Service, Ministry of Livestock, Agriculture and Fisheries], Montevideo, Uruguay

Summary
Report type: immediate notification
Date of start of the event: 7 Jun 2018
Date of confirmation of the event: 11 Jun 2018
Reason for notification: unexpected change in the distribution or increase in morbidity or mortality of a listed disease
Summary description: an increase of cases in horses with respiratory signs compatible with influenza was observed in several stud farms, breeding sport horses, in the cities of Salto and Paysandu.
Manifestation of disease: clinical disease
Causal agent: Influenza A virus
Serotype: not typed
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country.

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: unknown or inconclusive, Fomites (humans, vehicles, feed, etc.)
Epidemiological comments: following the disease situation reported in the region, since the beginning of the year [2018], due to the increase in the number of cases of equine influenza, the Official Veterinary Services of Uruguay have been vigilant and implemented weekly epidemiological surveillance actions urging equestrian institutions, private veterinarians, and owners to have the vaccinations updates and to notify any suspected cases of the disease.

Disease impact
Increased / Department / Specie / Change
Morbidity / Paysandu / Equidae / 0 equal or greater than 4
Morbidity / Salto / Equidae / 0 equal or greater than 4

Control measures
Measures applied: movement control inside the country; screening; quarantine; vaccination permitted (if a vaccine exists); no treatment of affected animals
Measures to be applied: no other measures

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type / Species / Test / Test date / Result
Division of Veterinary Laboratories (DILAVE) (national laboratory) / Equidae / real-time PCR / 11 Jun 2018 / Positive

Future reporting
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

